name: Super Easy Chicken Fingers
author: Trudi Davidoff
summary: These strips are so easy to make. They are my family's favorite. They also are good on rolls or bread for a yummy sandwich.
ingredients: 1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cut into bite size pieces
1 ¼ cups Italian seasoned bread crumbs
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Roll chicken pieces in the melted butter or margarine, then roll in the breadcrumbs Bake the chicken fingers in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes
Turn them over and cook for another 10 minutes or until they are brown and pierce easily with a fork
